records.addlTxt:
Defendant Mathew A Tombari in court with Attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.  Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Counts #1 & 2.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1 & 2.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Sonderhouse makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS HUBER    

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS    **may terminate after 12 months, if deemed appropriate by agent**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with:  Nicole T. (except for issues regarding the children) 

COSTS:  $343.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation)


COUNT #2:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS HUBER     **Consecutive to Count #1**

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS    **may terminate after 12 months, if deemed appropriate by agent**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with:  Nicole T. (except for issues regarding the children) 

COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:   30 Days,  Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion
